# Optional EOD Discord channels (one Cmd+K query per line)
#
# Discord is skipped by default. Use this file only when the user explicitly
# asks the eod skill to include Discord context.
#
# During an explicit Discord pass, the eod skill can scan:
#
#   Pass 1: Discord Inbox (cross-server @-mentions to you)
#   Pass 2: Server search `from:<you> after:<today>` (your posts)
#   Pass 3: This file - channels to read in full regardless of mentions or your own messages
#
# Pass 3 exists for channels where signal happens WITHOUT @-mentions and
# WITHOUT you posting - typically bot-driven channels like #alerts (Sentry
# release errors), #deployments (CI status), or #github (PR notifications
# routed without per-person tagging).
#
# DO NOT list every channel you're in. Pass 1 and Pass 2 already cover any
# channel where you participated. Pass 3 is for the long tail of bot channels.
#
# Format: <channel> <server> - exactly what you'd type into Discord's Cmd+K
# quick-switcher. Comments (#-prefixed) and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Recommended scan set for an engineering EOD:
#   alerts <server>        - Sentry / release-error notifications
#   deployments <server>   - CI deploy status, release announcements
#   github <server>        - GitHub webhook events (if your team routes them here)
#
# Example:
# alerts engineering
# deployments engineering
# github engineering
#
# Leaving this file empty is valid. Add lines only when you explicitly request
# Discord context and notice the EOD missing context that lived in a bot channel.
